@Carreau and I talked a bit about this further and he made the point that you might be running with a different profile from `default` but not know it, in which case it is perhaps better to make it explicit. However, I think it would be better for users to be able to just install the nbextension from the command line and not have to specify the default profile -- because probably 99% of people who are running it from the command line will be using the default profile. So here's a suggestion for a compromise:

* make the default for the command line option be `default`
* make there be *no* default profile in the function signatures -- just have it be a regular argument -- so you don't accidentally try to install it into the `None` profile, but you do still have to be explicit about what profile you're installing to

